'''Space Jam''' is a series of space-themed [[Worlds|world]] jams, held by VRChat, and in partnership with the [https://www.nssa.com.au/ National Space Society of Australia] (NSSA). Guided by the vision of the NSSA, creators are challenged to create immersive experiences to explore the frontiers of lunar exploration. Top winners of the jam receive varying prizes from the NSSA.

== National Space Society of Australia ==
The '''National Space Society of Australia''' (NSSA) is an independent nonprofit, educational organization dedicated to the creation of a spacefaring civilization. They are the partner of the Space Jam contests, which oversees the themes, sponsoring prizes, and some judging of worlds with VRChat.

=== Vision and mission ===
The vision, and mission of the NSSA, is to have people living and working in thriving communities beyond Earth, and to promote social, economic, technological, and political changes to expand civilization beyond Earth; to build a hopeful and prosperous future for humanity.

Their vision and mission, inspire the categories of their hosted Space Jams.

