=== Space Jam 2024 ===
''Main article: [[Space Jam 2024]]''
[[File:Space Jam .png|thumb|Space Jam 2024 - Key Art]]
'''Space Jam 2024''' was the first installment of Space Jam. Submissions opened up on March 1st, 2024 and closed on April 5th, 2024.

The objective of this jam was to "''create a VR experience that pushes the boundaries of virtual reality to depict the future of human life and work in space.''"

=== Space Jam 2025 ===
''Main article: [[Space Jam 2025]]''
[[File:SpaceJam 2025 KA.png|thumb|Space Jam 2025 - Key Art]]
'''Space Jam 2025''', also known as ''Space Jam 2'', is the second installment of Space Jam. Submissions opened up on February 24th, 2025 and closed on April 5th, 2025.

The objective of this jam is to "''create a VR experience that presents a hopeful vision of human life in space.''"

This jam had two categories that world creators could work on: 
* Sustainable Space, Resilient Earth
* New Horizons, Shared Futures 

=== Space Jam 2026 ===
''Main article: [[Space Jam 2026]]''
[[File:SpaceJam2026.webp|thumb|Space Jam 2026 - Key Art]]
'''Space Jam 2026''', also known as ''Space Jam 3'', is the third installment of Space Jam. Submissions opened up on February 18th, 2026 and closed on April 5th, 2026.

This jam focuses on world creators and film creators. Creators objective is to create a world or film that match the [https://nss.org/wp-content/uploads/NSS-Philosophy-Statement.pdf philosophy of the NSS].

